what's the low-down?

616
00:34:05,336 --> 00:34:07,568
Ha. No kidding, Sherry.
I doubted you'd remember me.

617
00:34:07,668 --> 00:34:08,271
No?

618
00:34:08,371 --> 00:34:10,875
Gee, It must be all of
five or six years ago.

619
00:34:11,544 --> 00:34:13,031
Hmm. It's eleven, to be exact.

620
00:34:13,278 --> 00:34:14,255
Don't be vulgar.

621
00:34:14,454 --> 00:34:16,616
Eleven years ago I was
still in finishing school.

622
00:34:17,057 --> 00:34:18,829
Aha. And I was a boy scout.

623
00:34:19,542 --> 00:34:20,530
Oh yeah. Ha.

624
00:34:21,029 --> 00:34:22,937
What good deed might
you be doing in Paris?

625
00:34:23,124 --> 00:34:25,354
I just told you.
I'm going to put on a revue.

626
00:34:25,772 --> 00:34:27,389
And you are going to star in it.
- Ha.

627
00:34:27,654 --> 00:34:29,110
Not a chance.
- Why not?

628
00:34:30,566 --> 00:34:32,104
Oh. Afraid of His Nibs, huh?

629
00:34:32,432 --> 00:34:34,724
Say, I've got to hand it
to that bird. He's smart.

630
00:34:34,974 --> 00:34:36,977
The Grand Duchess Alex.
That's marvellous.

631
00:34:37,359 --> 00:34:39,343
He's put you across in Paris
like a real showman.

632
00:34:39,732 --> 00:34:41,337
He's put me across? Ha.

633
00:34:41,590 --> 00:34:42,749
I've put myself across.

634
00:34:43,947 --> 00:34:45,281
He thinks I'm on the level.

635
00:34:46,428 --> 00:34:48,067
He does?
- Certainly.

636
00:34:50,432 --> 00:34:51,491
Well, well, well.

637
00:34:52,858 --> 00:34:54,161
That is practically perfect.

638
00:34:56,599 --> 00:34:57,443
What's this?

639
00:34:58,128 --> 00:35:00,172
That is your contract
to star in my revue.

640
00:35:00,347 --> 00:35:02,224
Don't be ridiculous, Sherry.
I won't sign this.

641
00:35:03,148 --> 00:35:04,249
Oh, I think you will.

642
00:35:04,600 --> 00:35:05,272
Mabel.

643
00:35:05,616 --> 00:35:08,674
