10,000 was your limit?

655
00:35:44,338 --> 00:35:46,678
For $10,000 you couldn't
put on a flea circus.

656
00:35:46,969 --> 00:35:49,846
But I don't want to put on a flea
circus. I want to sell ostrich plumes.

657
00:35:50,124 --> 00:35:53,711
Didn't you say that there was $50,000 in
it for me if I put your feathers across?

658
00:35:53,969 --> 00:35:55,752
Yes I did, but you
got to sell them first.

659
00:35:56,402 --> 00:35:57,650
My dear Joe.

660
00:35:57,912 --> 00:36:01,092
Can't you see this revue is precisely
the thing that's going to sell them?

661
00:36:01,295 --> 00:36:03,330
Millions of them.
- Yeah? Ten is my limit.

662
00:36:05,391 --> 00:36:06,607
Mr Baroque on the phone.

663
00:36:07,782 --> 00:36:09,198
Excuse me just a moment, please.

664
00:36:12,919 --> 00:36:14,037
Take care of Joe.

665
00:36:19,354 --> 00:36:21,034
Hello? Monsieur Nash?

666
00:36:22,187 --> 00:36:24,376
I would like to see you
regarding this revue.

667
00:36:24,604 --> 00:36:26,891
In which you propose to present
the Grand Duchess at.

668
00:36:27,316 --> 00:36:30,161
Monsieur Baroque .. it will be a
pleasure and a privilege to meet you.

669
00:36:31,159 --> 00:36:34,697
Of course I am pretty busy, but I will
gladly put aside my other engagements.

670
00:36:35,072 --> 00:36:36,946
I am sure if could see
you for a few moments ..

671
00:36:37,094 --> 00:36:39,677
We could arrange matters
to the satisfaction of ..

672
00:36:40,611 --> 00:36:41,486
Both of us.

673
00:36:41,726 --> 00:36:42,755
Quite right.

674
00:36:43,474 --> 00:36:44,443
Au revoir.

675
00:36:45,828 --> 00:36:47,081
Practically signed up.

676
00:36:48,584 --> 00:36:49,592
Don't be crude.

677
00:36:50,232 --> 00:36:51,449
Ha-ha-ha.

678
00:36:53,421 --> 00:36:54,208
Gentlemen.

679
00:36:54,560 --> 00:36:56,959
Monsieur Baroque and the
Duchess will be here in ten minutes.

680
00:36:57,422 --> 00:36:59,240
Now we've got to
put on the dog for this.

681
00:36:59,340 --> 00:37:00,498
Then you don't need me.

682
00:37:00,899 --> 00:37:03,347
On the contrary, Senator.
- Senator?

683
00:37:03,798 --> 00:37:06,538
You are Senator Ward.
You are financing this show.

684
00:37:06,805 --> 00:37:08,620
Oh, no I'm not. No, no ..

685
00:37:08,921 --> 00:37:10,152
Don't worry about that.

686
00:37:10,531 --> 00:37:12,622
Just sit still and look like a senator.

687
00:37:21,704 --> 00:37:22,719
Bonjour, Monsieur.

688
00:37:23,957 --> 00:37:25,003
Hello.

689
00:37:27,969 --> 00:37:29,042
Won't you be seated?

690
00:37:35,573 --> 00:37:36,805
[ Door knocks ]

691
00:37:38,784 --> 00:37:40,376
They are here. Here is his card.

692
00:37:41,036 --> 00:37:41,680
Uhoh.

693
00:37:45,188 --> 00:37:47,016
There you are .. senator.

694
00:37:47,837 --> 00:37:48,481
Lynn.

695
00:37:49,611 --> 00:37:50,560
Take a letter.

696
00:37:55,046 --> 00:37:55,947
Just a minute.

697
00:38:03,442 --> 00:38:04,318
Alright.

698
00:38:05,647 --> 00:38:07,580
Yes, Monsieur Savarin, I'll be ..

699
00:38:09,195 --> 00:38:10,211
I'll be delighted.

700
00:38:10,682 --> 00:38:12,707
Yes, the contracts are all ready.

701
00:38:13,112 --> 00:38:15,868
They are just awaiting your
signature, Monsieur Savarin.

702
00:38:17,386 --> 00:38:19,469
Mr Nash will see you now.
Will you step in, please.

703
00:38:20,039 --> 00:38:21,226
Oh yes, yes.

704
00:38:22,119 --> 00:38:23,986
I'll be expecting you, Mr Savarin.

705
00:38:25,157 --> 00:38:26,069
Au revoir.

706
00:38:28,218 --> 00:38:28,804
Ah.

707
00:38:30,132 --> 00:38:31,119
Monsieur Baroque.

708
00:38:31,220 --> 00:38:32,594
I'm charmed.
