00:41:58,909 --> 00:41:59,696
It worked.

778
00:42:01,538 --> 00:42:02,451
So I see.

779
00:42:03,420 --> 00:42:05,436
Well, what's the matter, honey?
Aren't you pleased?

780
00:42:06,116 --> 00:42:08,680
We stand to make a fortune out of this.
You can't tell where we'll end.

781
00:42:08,844 --> 00:42:10,117
Oh, I know where we'll end.

782
00:42:10,916 --> 00:42:13,021
I don't see why you
don't have faith in me.

783
00:42:13,293 --> 00:42:14,800
Well, look in the mirror and see.

784
00:42:52,187 --> 00:42:53,836
How about a little relaxez-vous?

785
00:43:40,800 --> 00:43:42,757
Senator. Are you ready
for a still picture?

786
00:43:42,930 --> 00:43:44,403
Just a moment, now. Just a moment.

787
00:43:45,004 --> 00:43:45,848
What the ..?

788
00:43:49,616 --> 00:43:50,517
There you are.

789
00:43:50,622 --> 00:43:51,866
Hold it .. still.

790
00:43:52,697 --> 00:43:53,393
Voila.

791
00:43:53,493 --> 00:43:55,070
Fine. Now let's get one with Nash.

792
00:43:56,035 --> 00:43:57,389
That's the second act finale.

793
00:43:57,679 --> 00:43:59,066
I practically wrote it for you.

794
00:43:59,553 --> 00:44:01,198
Suppose you say the rest with the music.

795
00:44:01,623 --> 00:44:03,322
Come on. Do a Helen Morgan.

796
00:44:03,758 --> 00:44:04,974
Sit there and inspire me.

797
00:44:05,293 --> 00:44:06,022
Alright.

798
00:44:10,256 --> 00:44:12,194
Oh Mr Nash, I've been looking for you.

799
00:44:12,294 --> 00:44:14,086
Oh yes?
- What do you think of that?

800
00:44:14,702 --> 00:44:15,317
Say.

801
00:44:15,877 --> 00:44:17,611
What do you think of
that for a fan, huh?

802
00:44:17,711 --> 00:44:18,679
A fan?
- Yeah.

803
00:44:19,062 --> 00:44:20,449
Why that is a complete costume.

804
00:44:36,339 --> 00:44:37,755
Snap.
- You're right, governor.

805
00:44:40,033 --> 00:44:40,919
Lynn.

806
00:44:46,948 --> 00:44:49,574
Too bad you don't get along better
with our young American composer.

807
00:44:49,674 --> 00:44:51,632
Oh, Jimmy is a darling.
Don't you like him?

808
00:44:52,133 --> 00:44:53,894
My passion for him
is well under control.

809
00:44:53,994 --> 00:44:55,467
Mr Nash, Peter is looking for you.

810
00:44:55,710 --> 00:44:56,783
I'll be right there.

811
00:44:57,896 --> 00:44:59,875
Are you lunching with me today?
- If you like.

812
00:45:05,957 --> 00:45:06,629
Oscar.

813
00:45:07,143 --> 00:45:09,890
Do go and see if my second act
costume is ready for fitting, yes?

814
00:45:10,483 --> 00:45:11,384
Tout de suite.

815
00:45:14,812 --> 00:45:16,563
Ah, bonjour Monsieur.
- Bonjour Monsieur.

816
00:45:16,866 --> 00:45:17,772
Your Highness.

817
00:45:18,183 --> 00:45:19,313
I say, that's not bad.

818
00:45:19,442 --> 00:45:21,061
Not bad? C'est magnifique.

819
00:45:23,925 --> 00:45:25,246
Oh Sherry.
- Yes?

820
00:45:25,717 --> 00:45:27,424
The Duchess, she wants help.

821
00:45:27,948 --> 00:45:29,021
Ah .. Your Highness.

822
00:45:30,010 --> 00:45:31,044
At your service.

823
00:45:36,741 --> 00:45:37,327
Oh.

824
00:45:38,715 --> 00:45:39,731
I beg your pardon.

825
00:45:43,070 --> 00:45:44,821
Say, what is this Lynn
girl to you anyway?

826
00:45:45,514 --> 00:45:48,398
Now don't you start. I'm having
enough trouble explaining you to her.

827
00:45:58,506 --> 00:46:00,093
Oh! You.

828
00:46:00,727 --> 00:46:02,464
Say Lynn, how about
having lunch with me?

829
00:46:02,681 --> 00:46:03,982
No thanks, Jimmy. Not today.

830
00:46:05,075 --> 00:46:06,148
You got other plans?

831
00:46:06,287 --> 00:46:09,556
Oh, I forgot. You're still carrying
a torch for that Nash, aren't you?

832
00:46:10,084 --> 00:46:11,954
Listen, Lynn. I'm crazy about you.

833
00:46:12,389 --> 00:46:14,542
Why don't you forget that worthless ..
- No account.

834
00:46:14,642 --> 00:46:16,044
Double-crossing.
- Two-timing.

835
00:46:16,144 --> 00:46:17,453
Unscrupulous.
- Unfaithful.

836
00:46:17,655 --> 00:46:19,552
Son of a ..
- So and so. It's no use, Jimmy.

837
00:46:20,104 --> 00:46:21,877
I can top every adjective
you can give me.

838
00:46:22,084 --> 00:46:23,555
I see. It's a case of ..

839
00:46:23,785 --> 00:46:26,636
Oh my man, I love him so.
He'll never go.

840
00:46:26,808 --> 00:46:27,782
Oh, stop it.

841
00:47:04,614 --> 00:47:06,360
Quick, quick. My next change.

842
00:47:07,047 --> 00:47:08,736
Oh baby, baby.

843
00:47:09,375 --> 00:47:10,889
Just in time to congratulate you.

844
00:47:10,989 --> 00:47:12,958
No kidding, Sherry. How was I?
Did they like me?

845
00:47:13,058 --> 00:47:16,166
Like you? Listen to them. If you're half
as good in the second act as the first.

846
00:47:16,625 --> 00:47:18,313
Well Duchess, they'll make a Queen.

847
00:47:47,838 --> 00:47:48,567
Senator.

848
00:47:59,489 --> 00:48:01,908
You want to make as much
money as possible, do you not?

849
00:48:02,008 --> 00:48:02,988
I certainly do.

850
00:48:03,088 --> 00:48:05,917
Now, you and I, Senator, can
rule the ostrich-feather world.

851
00:48:06,150 --> 00:48:07,549
No use. I'm tied up with Nash.

852
00:48:07,649 --> 00:48:10,682
What is tied can be untied by a
clever lawyer. I have an attorney.

853
00:48:10,847 --> 00:48:12,754
Yes, but I gave him
an option. He can sue.

854
00:48:12,945 --> 00:48:14,032
A scrap of paper.

855
00:48:14,710 --> 00:48:16,719
I can do more for you than this Nash.

856
00:48:17,230 --> 00:48:19,299
We will have my lawyer void the option.

857
00:48:19,629 --> 00:48:22,404
At the worst he can only sue us.
What else can he do?

858
00:48:22,845 --> 00:48:23,558
Oscar.

859
00:48:24,812 --> 00:48:25,885
You'll be surprised.

860
00:48:40,579 --> 00:48:43,177
[ Singing: ]

861
00:56:04,568 --> 00:56:05,669
Ladies and gentlemen.

862
00:56:05,991 --> 00:56:08,784
All the charm, all the glamour
you've seen this evening.

863
00:56:09,268 --> 00:56:11,780
Was presented, executed and designed ..

864
00:56:12,095 --> 00:56:15,567
By the energy, the enthusiasm
and the genius of one man.

865
00:56:16,990 --> 00:56:18,002
Mr Sherwood Nash.

866
00:56:29,984 --> 00:56:31,085
Ladies and gentlemen.

867
00:56:31,539 --> 00:56:34,633
I've always been told that
when good Americans die ..

868
00:56:35,332 --> 00:56:36,519
They don't go to heaven.

869
00:56:37,174 --> 00:56:38,217
They go to Paris.

870
00:56:40,961 --> 00:56:43,001
Smart Americans don't
wait until they die.

871
00:56:43,329 --> 00:56:44,883
They don't want to take any chances.

872
00:56:46,443 --> 00:56:47,258
My friends.

873
00:56:47,655 --> 00:56:50,600
Tonight you have seen more
than the première of a revue.

874
00:56:51,337 --> 00:56:53,119
You have seen the birth of an idea.

875
00:56:54,017 --> 00:56:55,004
I am not content.

876
00:56:55,298 --> 00:56:57,605
Merely to give you fashion
over the footlights.

877
00:56:58,490 --> 00:57:00,563
I want to bring it to
you into your home.

878
00:57:01,518 --> 00:57:02,982
It is my plan therefore.

879
00:57:03,345 --> 00:57:05,467
To establish here in your great city.

880
00:57:05,872 --> 00:57:10,022
An institution dedicated to
the highest ideals of fashion.

881
00:57:10,539 --> 00:57:12,394
A temple of creative art.

882
00:57:12,871 --> 00:57:14,679
Where I may offer for your approval.

883
00:57:15,064 --> 00:57:18,126
The most advance
conceptions in modern style.

884
00:57:19,639 --> 00:57:21,525
This establishment I shall call ..

885
00:57:21,865 --> 00:57:23,209
Maison Elegance.

886
00:57:23,823 --> 00:57:24,724
Where I trust.

887
00:57:24,951 --> 00:57:27,593
I shall continue to have
the pleasure of catering ..

888
00:57:27,855 --> 00:57:29,966
To your discrimination and taste.

889
00:57:31,197 --> 00:57:32,326
It is my further hope.

890
00:57:32,920 --> 00:57:34,298
That Maison Elegance.

891
00:57:34,734 --> 00:57:36,498
Will prove a worthy successor.

892
00:57:36,848 --> 00:57:38,356
To the house of Oscar Baroque.

893
00:57:38,656 --> 00:57:40,551
Your reigning king of fashion.

894
00:57:41,115 --> 00:57:43,776
Who I learn .. is about to abdicate.

895
00:57:45,015 --> 00:57:45,981
I thank you.

896
00:57:58,303 --> 00:57:59,996
Alright?
- Governor, you wowed them.

897
00:58:00,286 --> 00:58:01,963
We'll put that guy on ice.

898
00:58:02,313 --> 00:58:03,041
Sold.

899
00:58:04,436 --> 00:58:06,255
Why, you crook. What does this mean?

900
00:58:06,650 --> 00:58:08,583
Oscar, I told you you'd be surprised.

901
00:58:09,050 --> 00:58:10,567
What about your contract with me?

902
00:58:10,845 --> 00:58:12,490
What is tied can be untied.

903
00:58:12,590 --> 00:58:13,992
You cannot break this contract.

904
00:58:14,092 --> 00:58:15,644
A contract? A piece of paper.

905
00:58:15,876 --> 00:58:19,068
You cannot bluff me. I am not to be
taken in. I am the king of fashion.

906
00:58:19,491 --> 00:58:20,961
Well for your information, Oscar.

907
00:58:21,251 --> 00:58:23,447
A king can always be taken by an ace.

908
00:58:47,673 --> 00:58:50,794
But they are beautiful. Tell me, does it
hurt the ostrich when they are plucked?

909
00:58:51,417 --> 00:58:54,617
Madame, our patented plucking
process is practically painless.

910
00:59:01,790 --> 00:59:04,077
Monsieur Nash, tell me.
I am so interested.

911
00:59:04,377 --> 00:59:06,372
Do you supervise all details of this?

912
00:59:06,798 --> 00:59:08,585
Even to the page girls' costumes?

913
00:59:08,818 --> 00:59:11,194
Oh yes, I take care of everything,
from the bottom up.

914
00:59:13,592 --> 00:59:15,305
How do you do.
- Monsieur Nash.

915
00:59:15,493 --> 00:59:17,159
I want you to do my entire trousseau.

916
00:59:17,259 --> 00:59:20,515
Bridal gown, going-away dress, lingerie.
You handle lingerie, don't you?

917
00:59:20,731 --> 00:59:22,805
Oh yes, I take care of that personally.

918
00:59:26,092 --> 00:59:27,075
Ah, thank you.

919
00:59:27,259 --> 00:59:29,485
You serve the most delicious caviar.

920
00:59:30,105 --> 00:59:32,139
Yes, it comes from contented sturgeons.

921
00:59:34,153 --> 00:59:35,315
Monsieur Nash.
- Yes?

922
00:59:35,415 --> 00:59:37,895
This is all very beautiful.
But where are the dresses?

923
00:59:38,292 --> 00:59:39,577
Ah, Madame. Have patience.

924
00:59:40,182 --> 00:59:41,654
My creations are like jewels.

925
00:59:42,004 --> 00:59:43,420
They require the proper setting.

926
00:59:53,037 --> 00:59:55,306
Monsieur, Monsieur.
Madame has just arrived.

927
01:00:06,840 --> 01:00:09,639
Sherry, it is late. You can't keep
those people waiting here all day.

928
01:00:09,936 --> 01:00:12,064
Don't worry baby. As long
as it is food, they'll wait.

929
01:00:14,209 --> 01:00:15,446
Governor .. here she is.

930
01:00:21,623 --> 01:00:23,334
The Grand Duchess, Alex.

931
01:00:33,098 --> 01:00:34,255
You're late, Duchess.

932
01:00:34,355 --> 01:00:36,658
If Baroque discovers I've been
here, I'll <i>be </i>the late Duchess.

933
01:00:36,940 --> 01:00:37,841
How do you do.

934
01:03:19,323 --> 01:03:21,350
I regret we haven't been
able to please you, Madam.

935
01:03:21,606 --> 01:03:24,001
They have nothing. We'll go
over to the Maison Elegance.

936
01:03:31,310 --> 01:03:32,732
Mesdames, Messieurs.

937
01:03:33,040 --> 01:03:36,769
We are all suffering at the hands
of this unscrupulous American.

938
01:03:37,833 --> 01:03:39,154
Your showroom, Savarin.

939
01:03:39,515 --> 01:03:40,759
And yours Madame DeVrille.

940
01:03:41,039 --> 01:03:42,507
And yours and yours and yours.

941
01:03:42,808 --> 01:03:43,939
Are as empty as mine.

942
01:03:44,433 --> 01:03:46,002
What are we going to do about it?

943
01:03:46,309 --> 01:03:47,124
My friends.

944
01:03:47,558 --> 01:03:49,892
I have here cables from
my agents in New York.

945
01:03:50,397 --> 01:03:52,257
Reports from my detectives in Paris.

946
01:03:53,123 --> 01:03:56,774
Proving that this Nash is selling
forged sketches in New York.

947
01:03:57,079 --> 01:03:57,793
What?

948
01:03:58,003 --> 01:03:59,278
Sketches signed 'Baroque'.

949
01:03:59,740 --> 01:04:00,852
Signed 'DeVrille'.

950
01:04:00,952 --> 01:04:01,998
Signed 'Savarin'.

951
01:04:02,098 --> 01:04:04,430
We must protect ourselves.
- Something must be done at once.

952
01:04:04,530 --> 01:04:05,790
Yes.
- Go to the police.

953
01:04:05,890 --> 01:04:07,421
Monsieur Baroque, what shall we do?

954
01:04:07,647 --> 01:04:11,187
I am glad to see that in this crisis
we cease to be competitors.

955
01:04:12,164 --> 01:04:14,748
We must unite to drive this
thief out of our country.

956
01:04:14,979 --> 01:04:15,708
Exactly.

957
01:04:15,808 --> 01:04:18,376
Here is my plan to get rid of Nash.

958
01:04:19,327 --> 01:04:22,397
We must get the feathers through customs
right away. When did the boat dock?

959
01:04:22,632 --> 01:04:24,705
Yesterday morning.
But it seems there's a hitch.

960
01:04:25,186 --> 01:04:27,815
Why don't you drive down to the Customs
House yourself and unhitch them?

961
01:04:27,915 --> 01:04:29,330
We're up to our eyes in orders.

962
01:04:29,430 --> 01:04:31,851
And cable California to step up
production. We're way behind.

963
01:04:32,248 --> 01:04:34,287
I've got 50,000 eggs all ready to hatch.

964
01:04:34,707 --> 01:04:36,652
Well women don't wear eggs.
They wear feathers.

965
01:04:36,887 --> 01:04:38,796
But you can't hurry
mother nature, Mr Nash.

966
01:04:38,896 --> 01:04:39,984
No, I suppose not.

967
01:04:40,183 --> 01:04:41,170
Say, I've got it.

968
01:04:42,455 --> 01:04:44,810
Women buy unborn baby
lamb for furs, don't they?

969
01:04:45,239 --> 01:04:45,856
Yes.

970
01:04:46,348 --> 01:04:48,992
We'll ship the eggs over here and
sell them unborn baby ostrich.

971
01:04:49,227 --> 01:04:50,394
That's great, great.

972
01:04:50,556 --> 01:04:52,859
On your way, Senator.
- Just as soon as I have a drop of luck.

973
01:04:53,915 --> 01:04:56,570
Now, are you going to do it?
Tell me, what time will you be there?

974
01:04:57,362 --> 01:04:58,760
I didn't quite get that, honey.

975
01:04:59,354 --> 01:05:00,611
What time, Cheri?

976
01:05:01,113 --> 01:05:01,757
Snap.

977
01:05:03,712 --> 01:05:04,871
You're right, governor.

978
01:05:05,060 --> 01:05:05,704
What?

979
01:05:06,345 --> 01:05:07,389
Something I forgot.

980
01:05:09,319 --> 01:05:12,242
Don't you see, Lynn? You simply have to
make up your mind as I'm going away.

981
01:05:12,602 --> 01:05:14,754
You're leaving the show?
- Yes, I'm going to Berlin.

982
01:05:15,826 --> 01:05:16,985
Won't you come with me?

983
01:05:17,381 --> 01:05:18,707
I'm asking you to marry me.

984
01:05:19,169 --> 01:05:20,242
I don't know, Jimmy.

985
01:05:20,357 --> 01:05:22,717
Don't be such a little fool.
You know Nash will never marry you.

986
01:05:23,055 --> 01:05:24,592
How can you go on believing in him?

987
01:05:24,692 --> 01:05:27,532
He said he'd quit after the show didn't
he? Look at this. He'll never quit.

988
01:05:27,632 --> 01:05:30,072
He'll drag you from racket to racket.
- Jimmy. Please stop this.

989
01:05:30,307 --> 01:05:33,632
He's just using you. You do all the work
while he fools around with the Duchess.

990
01:05:34,122 --> 01:05:34,860
I see.

991
01:05:35,589 --> 01:05:36,778
Dirty work, huh?

992
01:05:37,362 --> 01:05:38,811
I must see you alone at once.

993
01:05:39,275 --> 01:05:40,754
Yes, something very important.

994
01:05:41,309 --> 01:05:42,754
Can't you tell me over the phone?

995
01:05:44,997 --> 01:05:45,726
Alright.

996
01:05:45,963 --> 01:05:46,835
I'll be here.

997
01:05:47,576 --> 01:05:48,363
Au revoir.

998
01:05:54,449 --> 01:05:56,096
I love you Lynn. I could make you happy.

999
01:05:57,973 --> 01:05:59,430
Am I interrupting a sale?

1000
01:05:59,602 --> 01:06:01,104
I hope you heard what I was saying.

1001
01:06:01,306 --> 01:06:03,782
The lyrics are charming. You must
let me hear the music sometime.

1002
01:06:03,882 --> 01:06:06,092
I'm trying to persuade Lynn
to forget you and marry me.

1003
01:06:07,724 --> 01:06:09,941
If she's smart, that's probably
what she would do.

1004
01:06:11,117 --> 01:06:12,133
Did you hear that?

1005
01:06:12,384 --> 01:06:13,600
Sherry, do you mean that?

1006
01:06:14,054 --> 01:06:15,785
Do you really want me
to go away with him?

1007
01:06:16,983 --> 01:06:17,970
No baby, I don't.

1008
01:06:19,067 --> 01:06:21,187
But he'd probably make you
much happier than I would.

1009
01:06:31,922 --> 01:06:33,309
Darling, will you come with me?

1010
01:06:33,582 --> 01:06:35,470
Oh Jimmy, I don't know what to do.

1011
01:06:35,758 --> 01:06:38,304
You know when my train is.
Will you try and make up your mind?

1012
01:06:38,596 --> 01:06:39,617
Yes, I'll try.

1013
01:06:56,063 --> 01:06:57,279
Are you in love with him?

1014
01:06:57,475 --> 01:06:59,849
Jimmy is a grand person
and he's the soul of honor.

1015
01:07:00,508 --> 01:07:01,438
And I'm a heel?

1016
01:07:01,575 --> 01:07:03,588
Don't be so funny.
- Baby.

1017
01:07:04,222 --> 01:07:05,451
I'll make you a promise.

1018
01:07:05,551 --> 01:07:07,075
I'm so tired of your promises.

1019
01:07:07,300 --> 01:07:08,745
But this one is different, honey.

1020
01:07:09,234 --> 01:07:10,021
I mean it.

1021
01:07:10,497 --> 01:07:11,228
Well ..

1022
01:07:11,526 --> 01:07:13,687
Give me two more weeks
to wind this up and I'll quit.

1023
01:07:13,851 --> 01:07:15,917
I'll cash in and we'll
go back to America.

1024
01:07:16,231 --> 01:07:17,809
What about your titled girlfriend?

1025
01:07:18,372 --> 01:07:20,397
When in the first place,
she isn't my girlfriend.

1026
01:07:20,497 --> 01:07:22,517
And in the second place,
her title is phony.

1027
01:07:23,650 --> 01:07:24,678
What do you mean?

1028
01:07:24,778 --> 01:07:28,109
I mean that the Grand Duchess Alex
is plain Mabel McGuire of Hoboken.

1029
01:07:28,386 --> 01:07:30,879
I knew her there eleven
years ago. Oh .. baby.

1030
01:07:31,668 --> 01:07:32,712
Your little finger.

1031
01:07:33,225 --> 01:07:35,701
Means more to me than all the
Mabel McGuires or Grand Duchesses ..

1032
01:07:35,801 --> 01:07:36,957
In all of Europe.

1033
01:07:37,057 --> 01:07:38,273
But you made love to her.

1034
01:07:38,513 --> 01:07:40,232
Well maybe I did.
I had to kid her along.

1035
01:07:40,332 --> 01:07:42,695
But on the level honey, she
doesn't mean a thing to me.

1036
01:07:43,601 --> 01:07:45,940
Well, I think you're lying
but you do it so beautifully.

1037
01:07:49,005 --> 01:07:49,591
Oh.

1038
01:07:51,791 --> 01:07:52,603
Oh, hello.

1039
01:07:53,258 --> 01:07:55,532
We were just talking about you.
Don't go, baby.

1040
01:07:56,709 --> 01:07:57,610
Well, Duchess.

1041
01:07:57,970 --> 01:07:59,357
What was it you had to tell me?

1042
01:07:59,678 --> 01:08:00,533
Nothing.

1043
01:08:01,397 --> 01:08:03,449
But over the phone, you said ..

1044
01:08:03,960 --> 01:08:06,218
I say now .. nuts.

1045
01:08:18,048 --> 01:08:18,692
Boss.

1046
01:08:19,160 --> 01:08:19,889
Yeah?

1047
01:08:19,989 --> 01:08:21,920
There's two mugs out there
that want to see you.

1048
01:08:22,642 --> 01:08:23,543
Let them wait.

1049
01:08:23,649 --> 01:08:26,017
No. They won't wait .. they're Cops.

1050
01:08:27,185 --> 01:08:28,029
Let them in.

1051
01:08:34,443 --> 01:08:35,884
Ah, bonjour Monsieur.

1052
01:08:36,470 --> 01:08:37,514
Won't you sit down.

1053
01:08:38,242 --> 01:08:39,125
Have a smoke.

1054
01:08:39,710 --> 01:08:41,183
This is no social visit, Monsieur.

1055
01:08:41,415 --> 01:08:42,937
I am from the Prefect Of Police.

1056
01:08:43,852 --> 01:08:44,502
Well.

1057
01:08:45,499 --> 01:08:47,224
You are charged Monsieur, with forgery.

1058
01:08:47,549 --> 01:08:49,672
Fraud, petty larceny and grand larceny.

1059
01:08:49,872 --> 01:08:54,320
Under paragraph 5, article 17 of the
criminal code of the Republic of France.

1060
01:08:54,935 --> 01:08:56,701
It is my duty to arrest you.

1061
01:08:57,498 --> 01:08:58,717
Who brings these charges?

1062
01:08:59,131 --> 01:09:00,166
As you will see.

1063
01:09:01,856 --> 01:09:03,294
Oscar Baroque. Oh.

1064
01:09:03,969 --> 01:09:08,040
On behalf of the Associated Couturiers
Protective Alliance of Paris. Well.

1065
01:09:08,745 --> 01:09:09,669
That's ducky.

1066
01:09:11,479 --> 01:09:12,152
Oh.

1067
01:09:13,001 --> 01:09:15,526
Monsieur, could I have a few
moments with my secretary?

1068
01:09:16,017 --> 01:09:16,804
Privately.

1069
01:09:17,462 --> 01:09:19,007
Oh, I'll not try to escape.

1070
01:09:19,485 --> 01:09:21,315
If Monsieur will give
me his word of honor.

1071
01:09:21,660 --> 01:09:22,819
By all means, Monsieur.

1072
01:09:26,787 --> 01:09:28,117
I told you this would happen.

1073
01:09:29,997 --> 01:09:33,060
You promised me you would quit.
- Baby, it's okay. I'll get out of this.

1074
01:09:33,273 --> 01:09:34,775
I don't care whether you do or not.

1075
01:09:34,875 --> 01:09:35,790
I'm through.

1076
01:09:35,890 --> 01:09:37,320
But honey, it's very simple.

1077
01:09:37,561 --> 01:09:39,416
All I've got to do is find the Duchess.

1078
01:09:39,870 --> 01:09:42,671
Then tell it to the Duchess.
I'm going to Berlin with Jimmy tonight.

1079
01:09:42,984 --> 01:09:44,743
But wait a minute, baby.
You can't do this.

1080
01:09:45,158 --> 01:09:46,578
You love me.
- No, I don't.

1081
01:09:47,399 --> 01:09:48,201
I don't.

1082
01:09:54,352 --> 01:09:55,110
Monsieur.

1083
01:09:55,288 --> 01:09:56,905
If you give me just half an hour ..

1084
01:09:57,005 --> 01:09:59,280
I'm quite sure this little
misunderstanding can be settled.

1085
01:09:59,380 --> 01:10:00,539
By all means, Monsieur.

1086
01:10:00,875 --> 01:10:02,839
But we will have to go with
you wherever you go.

1087
01:10:03,204 --> 01:10:04,714
Monsieur, it's a pleasure. Come on.

1088
01:10:07,210 --> 01:10:10,086
I must see you. Just a moment, Mr Nash.
- Some other time, Senator.

1089
01:10:10,276 --> 01:10:12,318
About those feathers.
- We'll get together again.

1090
01:10:12,907 --> 01:10:14,154
But they are all diseased.

1091
01:10:15,633 --> 01:10:16,432
Diseased?

1092
01:10:16,532 --> 01:10:19,083
Yeah. The entire cargo was confiscated
by the French Board of Health.

1093
01:10:19,306 --> 01:10:20,465
They are all condemned.

1094
01:10:21,286 --> 01:10:22,817
When did you hear this?
- Just now.

1095
01:10:23,610 --> 01:10:25,394
You haven't heard a thing. Get me?
- Yeah.

1096
01:10:44,691 --> 01:10:46,844
So nice to see you all. Just lovely.

1097
01:10:47,026 --> 01:10:48,188
All my darlings.

1098
01:10:48,648 --> 01:10:49,552
Monsieur Nash.

1099
01:10:53,952 --> 01:10:56,123
Ah, I see I'm just in time
to congratulate you.

1100
01:10:56,366 --> 01:10:58,983
How dare you come here.
- Oh, I'm leaving in a moment.

1101
01:10:59,800 --> 01:11:02,541
Just as soon as you tell this gentleman
that there's been a little mistake.

1102
01:11:02,714 --> 01:11:04,020
There has been <i>no</i> mistake.

1103
01:11:04,253 --> 01:11:06,038
I swore out the complaint myself.

1104
01:11:07,429 --> 01:11:09,618
Don't you think there has been
a little mistake, precious?

1105
01:11:09,718 --> 01:11:12,052
Sir, you will address Her
Highness by her correct title.

1106
01:11:12,512 --> 01:11:14,290
Would you really like me to do that?

1107
01:11:14,920 --> 01:11:16,780
Perhaps you have been
a little hasty, darling.

1108
01:11:16,880 --> 01:11:18,470
No, I have delayed too long.

1109
01:11:18,676 --> 01:11:19,577
Take him away.

1110
01:11:20,418 --> 01:11:21,701
Just a moment.

1111
01:11:22,327 --> 01:11:25,444
Monsieur Baroque, I have something to
tell you. Something rather personal.

1112
01:11:26,459 --> 01:11:28,419
If you'll take a tip from me,
you'll listen to it.

1113
01:11:29,064 --> 01:11:29,943
In private.

1114
01:11:30,043 --> 01:11:31,122
Monsieur.
- Oscar.

1115
01:11:41,500 --> 01:11:42,812
Why did you bring him here?

1116
01:11:43,528 --> 01:11:46,837
He asked if he might drop in for
a moment on his way to jail.

1117
01:11:47,325 --> 01:11:49,595
Sherry .. are you going to
spill the beans about me?

1118
01:11:49,900 --> 01:11:51,397
Not if you call your husband off.

1119
01:11:51,497 --> 01:11:53,567
But I can't. He's determined
to put you behind bars.

1120
01:11:53,779 --> 01:11:56,711
But I don't like it behind bars. I'm
sorry Mabel, but it's my only weapon.

1121
01:11:56,913 --> 01:11:57,814
What about me?

1122
01:11:58,212 --> 01:11:59,084
Listen, baby.

1123
01:11:59,613 --> 01:12:02,060
The wedding is over. You've got
him, haven't you? He's hooked.

1124
01:12:02,388 --> 01:12:04,691
What can happen to you?
- He could have the marriage annulled.

1125
01:12:05,087 --> 01:12:06,789
What, and be the
laughing stock of Paris?

1126
01:12:06,889 --> 01:12:07,724
Oh no.

1127
01:12:11,008 --> 01:12:12,360
Well, what have you to say?

1128
01:12:13,921 --> 01:12:14,908
Monsieur Baroque.

1129
01:12:15,401 --> 01:12:18,800
Before they drag me off to the Bastille,
I'd like to tell you a little story.

1130
01:12:19,342 --> 01:12:21,838
And let you decide whether or
not I shall tell it to the press.

1131
01:12:22,098 --> 01:12:25,165
This is a story of someone
very near and dear to you.

1132
01:12:25,581 --> 01:12:26,273
Well?

1133
01:12:26,373 --> 01:12:27,017
Well.

1134
01:12:27,778 --> 01:12:30,755
Years ago, in the lovely
American city of Hoboken.

1135
01:12:31,651 --> 01:12:34,377
There was born to Mr and
Mrs Elmer McGuire ..

1136
01:12:34,635 --> 01:12:36,678
A beautiful, bonny little baby girl.

1137
01:12:37,188 --> 01:12:38,375
Whom they named 'Mabel'.

1138
01:12:38,528 --> 01:12:40,376
This does not mean anything to me.

1139
01:12:40,584 --> 01:12:42,315
Oh, you're not interested
in little Mabel?

1140
01:12:42,511 --> 01:12:43,412
Now let's see.

1141
01:12:45,139 --> 01:12:47,382
Would you by any chance be
interested in birthmarks?

1142
01:12:47,871 --> 01:12:48,959
Birthmarks?
- Yes.

1143
01:12:49,267 --> 01:12:51,757
Birthmarks. Mabel had one. Yes indeed.

1144
01:12:52,339 --> 01:12:54,775
She had the cutest
little strawberry mark.

1145
01:12:54,972 --> 01:12:57,722
In the most unusual and
interesting location.

1146
01:13:01,772 --> 01:13:03,587
What proof have you of this?

1147
01:13:03,887 --> 01:13:05,847
Aside from the strawberry mark? Well ..

1148
01:13:06,353 --> 01:13:08,011
There is Elmer McGuire, her father.

1149
01:13:08,493 --> 01:13:11,131
As able and conscientious a
bootlegger as ever faked a gin label.

1150
01:13:11,326 --> 01:13:13,136
I'm sure he'd be able to identify her.

1151
01:13:13,722 --> 01:13:14,775
Is this true?

1152
01:13:14,980 --> 01:13:16,037
But darling.

1153
01:13:16,429 --> 01:13:19,245
You swore it was me
you loved. Not my title.

1154
01:13:19,412 --> 01:13:21,873
You've tricked me. You're an imposter.
- Oh, pipe down.

1155
01:13:21,973 --> 01:13:23,828
Quit yelling, you cheap
little dressmaker.

1156
01:13:23,928 --> 01:13:24,888
You are a fraud.

1157
01:13:24,988 --> 01:13:26,879
You tricked me into marriage.
- Tricked you?

1158
01:13:26,979 --> 01:13:29,880
Who wanted this marriage in the first
place? You know, you're no bargain.

1159
01:13:29,980 --> 01:13:32,086
You begged and pleaded. Why?

1160
01:13:32,431 --> 01:13:34,992
So I'll bring customers into your shop.
- I'll have you put in prison.

1161
01:13:35,434 --> 01:13:37,285
Maybe we'll get adjoining cells.
- Go ahead.

1162
01:13:37,672 --> 01:13:40,001
Just try to put me in jail.
Just you try.

1163
01:13:40,173 --> 01:13:43,867
Oh boy. I can spill more dirt about you
and some of your pretty little habits ..

1164
01:13:44,095 --> 01:13:45,940
You are shameless.
- Go ahead. I'm all for it.

1165
01:13:46,137 --> 01:13:48,755
They've not had a good laugh in Paris
for years. Let's give them a break.

1166
01:13:48,924 --> 01:13:50,211
'Madame Baroque tells all'.

1167
01:13:50,520 --> 01:13:52,193
'The love life of a dressmaker'.

1168
01:13:52,293 --> 01:13:54,628
That would ruin me.
- You said a mouthful.

1169
01:13:54,808 --> 01:13:56,977
But Monsieur, no-one need know.

1170
01:13:57,530 --> 01:14:00,830
It was my very good fortune to
meet Her Highness years ago, but ..

1171
01:14:01,498 --> 01:14:02,800
I am the soul of discretion.

1172
01:14:04,941 --> 01:14:07,507
Monsieur, I cannot wait any longer.
I must take the defendant.

1173
01:14:08,191 --> 01:14:11,028
Monsieur Baroque, don't you think now
that there has been a little mistake?

1174
01:14:11,535 --> 01:14:13,277
I will withdraw the charges.

1175
01:14:15,462 --> 01:14:16,108
Well?

1176
01:14:16,565 --> 01:14:17,409
That's that.

1177
01:14:18,346 --> 01:14:19,016
Now.

1178
01:14:20,050 --> 01:14:20,990
What is this?

1179
01:14:21,192 --> 01:14:23,512
This is a contract to
purchase Maison Elegance.

1180
01:14:23,700 --> 01:14:25,396
The most flourishing business in Paris.

1181
01:14:25,773 --> 01:14:27,428
Send a porter up for my things will you.

1182
01:14:27,623 --> 01:14:28,712
And call a taxi.

1183
01:14:29,327 --> 01:14:30,858
Yes. For the Berlin Express.

1184
01:14:32,643 --> 01:14:33,683
Alright, Tibby.

1185
01:14:34,141 --> 01:14:35,418
Now we're ready to go.

1186
01:14:37,648 --> 01:14:38,421
Voila.

1187
01:14:39,303 --> 01:14:40,330
Merci, Monsieur.

1188
01:14:40,589 --> 01:14:41,805
This includes everything.

1189
01:14:42,079 --> 01:14:44,785
Business, goodwill, fixtures
and of course the feathers.

1190
01:14:44,986 --> 01:14:46,460
Including the last big shipment.

1191
01:14:46,658 --> 01:14:48,678
Oh yes, indeed. <i>All</i> the feathers.

1192
01:14:49,501 --> 01:14:52,893
I .. regret that I can't remain
for your charming reception.

1193
01:14:53,597 --> 01:14:57,216
Monsieur, in America it is the custom
of good friends .. to kiss the bride.

1194
01:15:00,105 --> 01:15:02,469
In France, I understand
they also kiss the groom.

1195
01:15:04,408 --> 01:15:06,253
Au revoir, Monsieur. Your Highness.

1196
01:15:07,946 --> 01:15:08,985
Bon fortune.

1197
01:15:18,759 --> 01:15:21,319
But that's not my bag.
- No, baby. That's mine.

1198
01:15:22,189 --> 01:15:23,614
Why, I thought you were in jail.

1199
01:15:24,224 --> 01:15:26,419
What are you doing here?
- Taking you to the boat.

1200
01:15:26,960 --> 01:15:28,805
No you're not. I'm going
to Berlin with Jimmy.

1201
01:15:29,089 --> 01:15:31,117
You're going to American with me.
- Well, I'm not.

1202
01:15:31,327 --> 01:15:33,429
Oh yes you are. Look, baby.

1203
01:15:33,994 --> 01:15:35,153
I've sold the business.

1204
01:15:55,219 --> 01:15:55,920
Sherry.

1205
01:15:56,106 --> 01:15:58,841
Now that you've wriggled out of this,
you've got to make me a promise.

1206
01:15:59,352 --> 01:16:01,308
No more of your crazy schemes.

1207
01:16:01,698 --> 01:16:05,139
Honey, absolutely.
From now on, you're the Captain.

1208
01:16:05,470 --> 01:16:06,302
Mr Nash.

1209
01:16:07,497 --> 01:16:08,946
Mr Nash?
- Yes?

1210
01:16:09,715 --> 01:16:11,274
Would you mind looking into this box?

1211
01:16:15,369 --> 01:16:16,327
What do you see?

1212
01:16:17,434 --> 01:16:19,457
Looks like a lot of worms.
- Exactly.

1213
01:16:19,704 --> 01:16:21,964
Mr Nash, I have the most
wonderful proposition for you.

1214
01:16:22,486 --> 01:16:24,820
For years I have experimented
and at last I have succeeded.

1215
01:16:25,194 --> 01:16:27,998
I have succeeded in crossing
silkworms with glow-worms ..

1216
01:16:28,298 --> 01:16:29,943
To make luminous evening dresses.

1217
01:16:31,039 --> 01:16:33,258
Well .. gee, that's an idea.

1218
01:16:33,437 --> 01:16:36,977
Mr Nash, we can make old fabrics
glow like so many neon lights.

1219
01:16:37,384 --> 01:16:39,440
And you are the only man
in the world, Mr Nash ..

1220
01:16:39,540 --> 01:16:41,299
Who can put over this
marvellous discovery.

1221
01:16:41,798 --> 01:16:43,611
Think of the possibilities, Mr Nash.

1222
01:16:43,814 --> 01:16:45,621
Women's dresses glowing, scintillating.

1223
01:16:45,924 --> 01:16:48,864
Indoors, outdoors,
picnics, parties, balls.

1224
01:16:48,964 --> 01:16:50,408
We don't have to stop at dresses.

1225
01:16:50,826 --> 01:16:51,813
Why that's right.

1226
01:16:51,969 --> 01:16:54,460
We could make lingerie,
pyjamas, night dresses.

1227
01:16:54,560 --> 01:16:56,648
Of course. Are you a
married man, Mr Nash?

1228
01:16:58,105 --> 01:17:00,769
Wouldn't you like to see your
wife glowing in the darkness?

1229
01:17:02,687 --> 01:17:04,429
My worms. My worms!

1230
01:17:05,217 --> 01:17:06,972
My worms. My worms.

1231
01:17:07,324 --> 01:17:08,463
My worms.

1232
01:17:12,286 --> 01:17:12,937
Baby.

1233
01:17:13,692 --> 01:17:16,036
Do you know what you've done?
Do you see what you threw away?

1234
01:17:16,136 --> 01:17:18,724
Yes, I know. A chance to
make a million dollars.

1235
01:17:21,395 --> 01:17:22,511
I get you, Captain.

1236
01:17:30,777 --> 01:17:31,421
Snap.

1237
01:17:31,984 --> 01:17:33,386
Right, governor.

1238
01:17:49,744 --> 01:17:50,661
..s-d..
